verbose_text: Molecules of primary importance in cement dust in terms of content and potential health effects basically include 60-67% calcium oxide, 17-25 silicon oxide (SiO 2), and 3-5% aluminium (Al) oxide, with some amount of iron oxide, chromium (Cr), potassium, sodium, sulphur, and magnesium oxide [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR].
